    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-1440328">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-1440328">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,1440328)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-1440328">
																		Downvoted
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/echofourdelta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(515520); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=515520&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183142" alt="EchoFourDelta" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=515520)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/echofourdelta" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(515520); return false;" >EchoFourDelta</a></span> <span class="odate time_1336351861 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 May 2012 00:51</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1440328">
									

<p>For the sole purpose of the MTF commander's first words in the tale. Here is a not-too-often-seen chance to show how someone on the bleeding edge would react to something. Someone brought up the issue that he knows the O5 is listening. But do this. Pretend you're the MTF commander for a moment.</p>
<p>You lead this team of men, and have for years. You know each one of their faces, their quirks, their foibles, how they'll react, what their old jobs were, where they're from. Family. And now another one of these scrawny-ass, lab-coat-wearing, rat-fucked little bastards is standing in front of you telling you to pick one. Pick one to send out to perform a task you <strong>know</strong> is doomed to failure, something that you <strong>know</strong> is gonna end in his death, and likely others, and something that you <strong>know</strong> is make things worse. Worse than that? You know goddamn well that they could have some smooth-talking D-Class do it. Hell, get a legit former cop. Someone that went dirty. They don't need your boys, but they're gonna do it anyway, because those fucking retards don't know what it's like. They never leave their damn offices and labs. The closest they ever get is hearing the shit on a radio, watching helmet cams, and listening to the mission logs recorded side by side. Bunch of cocksuckers come into <strong>your</strong> office and ask for your men?</p>
<p>What's your response gonna be? A dull, muted, trite, stock, cliche phrase that oh-so-cleverly includes &quot;expunged&quot; and &quot;redacted&quot;? <strong>No</strong>. You're gonna tell that bastard what you really think. He's gonna wonder what half the curse words and turns of phrase you used even <strong>mean</strong>. He'll know that you despise him, and have nothing but contempt for his shallow, cloistered, cowardly ways, asking for things he can't do himself. It doesn't matter if God himself is listening.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Military Consultant, SCP Wiki</p>

				</div>
					
					
